  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0baf\u0ba9\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0bcb\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3 \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bcb\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The lotus tower that has become useless to the country",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "Many of the projects that have been undertaken in conjunction with China as development projects have become a burden to the country today and they have created a huge debt burden.",
        "With Sri Lanka facing the worst economic crisis today, even income-centric plans have become ineffective. The Lotus Tower is one such example.",
        "The lotus tower, which boasts of being the tallest tower in South Asia, has so far received no benefit to the country.",
        "Construction work on the Lotus Tower in central Colombo began on January 20, 2012. It took about 7 years to build the largest tower in South Asia.",
        "According to the Telecommunications Regulatory Commission of Sri Lanka, US $ 104.5 million has been spent on the construction of the Lotus Tower.",
        "The US Telecommunications Regulatory Commission of Sri Lanka has received US $ 67 million in funding from China and the rest has been spent.",
        "At 356 meters, it is considered to be the tallest tower in South Asia and the 19th tallest tower in the world, measuring 30,600 square feet.",
        "Parking facilities for about 200 vehicles are also provided at this place.",
        "It has been announced that Sri Lanka Television and Radio will be broadcasting light and digital technology in the near future through this tower.",
        "The first and second floors of the tower are reserved for television and radio services.",
        "The third and fourth floors of the Lotus Tower are used as halls for ceremonies. The 6th floor is said to have been built to occupy a very special place.",
        "That is, the restaurant, located on the 6th floor, is built to rotate. This gives people the opportunity to see the whole city of Colombo in the color of food.",
        "The 7th floor is reported to be located at the top of the tower and overlooks the city of Colombo.",
        "Built on the 7th floor, the tower is a niche tower that offers digital technology.",
        "A special feature of this tower with 8 elevators is that it is equipped with Sri Lanka's first high speed elevator which can reach 7 meters per second.",
        "With the construction of the Lotus Tower, it was expected that Sri Lanka's television and radio services would be digitalized in the near future and would greatly benefit the Sri Lankan national economy. But it is noteworthy that the Lotus Tower is not useful to the country today."
      ],
